Recruiters are officially cooked. Burnt. Charred. Medium-rare with a side of LinkedIn lunacy.

In today’s episode of “Why Is This App Like This?”, we break down recruiters losing their minds because candidates ask the audacity-filled question:

 “What’s the salary?”

Apparently that’s rude now.
Apparently paying rent is “shopping for numbers.”
Apparently you’re supposed to get emotionally invested in culture, vibes, growth potential, and imaginary carrots before knowing if you can afford groceries.
